The paper deals with language modeling, which is a central task in natural language processing (NLP), hence cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also explores various techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks and Long-Short Term Memory, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with large-scale language modeling, which involves handling large datasets and complex structures, hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely category. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of character-level models, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV), hence cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible category.
